    <text id="A8049T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Alexander asks McCue to settle a bond Alexander signed on his behalf that has
                    recently been called in.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Dr Alexander<lb/><hi rend="underline">1860</hi>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-03-09">March 9th. 1860</date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><unclear>Dr</unclear> John</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I saw D S Bell a few days since, and wants the money on that bond which I signed
                    for you. My funds are at a low ebb. and it would greatly inconvenience me to
                    have it to raise. Please make some arrangement of the matter &amp; greatly
                    oblige me. Let me hear from you about it at your <hi rend="underline"
                    >earliest</hi> convenience.</p>
                <p>We are all well--Baby's flourishing How is Liz:-we heard of her confinement but
                    nothing from her since. Why Dont you "come over". no news of interest</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">C. Alexander</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
